AGI - When in 2018 the first revelations about the encounter between Donald Trump and the pornstar Stormy Daniels, the then first lady Melania Trump was described as "furious". Six years later, she was the great absent from the trial that began yesterday in Manhattan and where her husband was accused of paying in black to buy the silence of pornstars and a former Playboy rabbit, who he would meet at the time he was already married to Melania, in the year, 2006, where his son Barron would be born: The former first lady did not show up alongside her husband in these hours, but according to the New York Times he would call "unjust" the trial and a "vergognose" electoral interference.
Judge Juan Merchan, who presides over the trial, Monday stated that the former first lady could be called to testify. This hypothesis, if confirmed, could embarrass Trump, because it is likely that the prosecution would repropose in the classroom some evidence collected in these years, including the famous tape released in 2016, in full election campaign, in which Trump had spoken to a friend about the "affirming female genitals".
<div </div
